Kazkommertsbank to Lend $1 Billion for Almaty Construction

-- B y   N a r i m a n   G i z i t d i n o v
-- 
2011-08-18T08:26:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/kazkommertsbank-to-lend-1-billion-for-almaty-construction-1-.html
Kazkommertsbank,  Kazakhstan ’s
largest lender by assets, will finance 150 billion tenge ($1
billion) of construction projects in the nation’s commercial
capital, Almaty, the city government said.  The bank will fund projects through 2012, allocating 75
billion tenge for home building and 60.3 billion tenge for
infrastructure and tourist venues, the municipality said in an
e-mailed statement today.  The lender will also provide 14.7 billion tenge for small
and medium-sized businesses and  mortgage loans , according to the
statement.  Kazkommertsbank will use its own funds for the projects,
Shynar Zhanibekova, a spokeswoman at the Almaty-based lender,
said by phone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nariman Gizitdinov in Almaty at 
 ngizitdinov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
